        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 5:01PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 5 miles north of Antelope Springs to 6
miles east of Deer Trail, or extending from 18 miles north of Fort
Morgan to 28 miles northwest of Limon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Brush, Merino, Hillrose, Gary, Woodrow, Twelve-Mile
Corner, Adena School, Shamrock, Midway, Woodlin School, Snyder,
Adena, Last Chance, Antelope Springs, Prewitt Reservoir,
Cottonwood Valley, Atwood, Union and Fremont Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
